President Trump met with four families in the Oval Office to discuss the need for tax cuts and reforms. The families expressed their support for tax relief and the positive impact it would have on their businesses and the economy. They also discussed the importance of job creation, choice in education, and the need for fair trade deals. The families presented the President with a wooden American flag as a token of their appreciation. President Trump highlighted the progress being made in the economy and the changes that have taken place in the country over the past 10 months.